---
description: Critter Quest project rules
alwaysApply: true
---
- Phaser 3 + TypeScript, strict mode. Never introduce `any` or non-null `!` without justification.
- Game logic lives in src/systems/ as pure functions; scenes (src/scenes/) only render and route input. Never put battle math in a scene.
- All randomness goes through the injectable Rng — never call Math.random directly in src/systems/ (planned; battle.ts still migrating).
- Content lives in src/data/ as typed tables; no gameplay constants inline — use src/data/constants.ts when added.
- After any change: npm run verify && npx tsc --noEmit must pass; npm run test:e2e for flow changes.
- Saves: never change PlayerState shape without bumping SAVE_KEY version and adding a migration + test.
- Keep files under ~300 lines; extract before they grow.
- Use trySave(scene) from src/utils/saveFeedback.ts instead of saveGame() in scenes.
